page.title: 08Deptford park trail
page.content: Go in the Grinstead road/ Evelyn street gate.Go straight up the path to the play-park.you will see alot of trees around the edges.the park keeper told us that the trees are mostly London plane, beech, cherry, almond, Indian bean which grows long black running beans, ash, tree of heaven hawthorne,2 horse chestnut, and silver birch. keep walking and you will see the paddling pool.In summer they clean the paddling pool and you use it and its popular.* keep walking straight.there are a lot of trees beside the cafe. the trees have got almonds on.keep walking and on the left you will see the running track. some schools use the running track for sports day and the grass around it has to be cut 2-3 times a week.turn left and walk around the running track and you will see the football pitch.
